Users of screen readers and other assistive technologies need information
about the behavior and purpose of controls on your web page.
Native HTML controls like buttons and radio groups
come with that information built in.
For custom controls you create,
[ARIA](https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#role_definitions)
roles and attributes let you provide functionality information.
(Learn more in the
[Introduction to ARIA](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/accessibility/semantics-aria/).)
